        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Apeejay School - Sector II"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Rahul Jalan"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-08-30",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Respected Mam/Moni Acharya/Shantona Maam\n\nGood Day\n\nNow that i look back i feel fortunate and overwhelmed to have completed my schooling from Apeejay School Saltlake.\n\nBut, on the contrary, it shattered me too. Though I don't want to dig old graves, I still distinctly recall you calling me a \" Drug Addict \".\n\nThe word devastated me as the same was openly called out to me. The reason best known to you.\n\nTill date when ever i think about it I get goosebumps. A teacher's projection is to motivate, inspire and boost a student irrespective of his behaviour in class. An amicable behaviour and consistent motivation helps a student to overcome it's hindrances and obstacles.\n\nWhen a child is in school every parent feels secure of it's child's education and not being abused or being demoralized or called upon with a psedeuo name. It's heart breaking.\n\nMy earnest request to you even today is please stop addressing such vulnerable words and endeavor to solve and overcome the stress the students are bestowed upon.\n\nMy sincere apologies to you if my message depicts disrespect to you.\n\nRegards Rahul Jalan",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
